"```sql\nSELECT \n    (SELECT COUNT(*) \n     FROM schools \n     WHERE County = 'Orange' \n       AND DOC = 54 \n       AND StatusType = 'Merged')::float / \n    (SELECT COUNT(*) \n     FROM schools \n     WHERE County = 'Orange' \n       AND DOC = 52 \n       AND StatusType = 'Merged') AS ratio\n```\nThis SQL query calculates the ratio of merged Unified School District schools to merged Elementary School District schools in Orange County. It uses the `DOC` values to identify the type of school district and filters by `StatusType` to find merged schools. The `::float` is used to ensure the division results in a floating-point number."